  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>conchiglie pasta</strong> to a large pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4 min</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-1.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-1.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-1.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-1.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-1.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil the kettle</p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>broccoli</strong> into small florets</p>\n<p>After 4 min add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> and cook for a further 4 min or until just cooked</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and transfer to a plate (or keep in the colander!), reserve the pan</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-2.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-2.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-2.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-2.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-2.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Tear the <strong>mozzarella</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Tip: </span>for a lower salt option, use half the stock cube</p>\n<p>Add 400ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>to the<strong> stock </strong>– this is your<strong> creamy stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-3.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-3.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-3.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-3.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-3.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 40g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [80g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in your reserved pot over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once melted, add 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>\n<p>Gradually whisk the <strong>creamy stock</strong> into the <strong>roux</strong>, a little at a time and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> béchamel sauce </strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-4.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-4.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-4.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-4.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1508.-step-4.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and half the <strong>grated cheddar</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
